you're taking

13:35.902 --> 13:37.294
this article
too personally?

13:37.338 --> 13:39.122
It's the piece about me
with a direct quote

13:39.166 --> 13:41.037
from my mom, so no,
and after my run-in

13:41.081 --> 13:42.473
with the Commission
on Judicial Performance,

13:42.517 --> 13:44.301
I don't need any heat.

13:44.345 --> 13:47.391
I wouldn't label it as heat.
More like harmless attention,

13:47.435 --> 13:49.437
with significant
entertainment value.

13:49.480 --> 13:51.439
Well, you saw Benner
this morning.She'll get over it.

13:51.482 --> 13:54.094
In the meantime, don't...Catastrophize?

13:54.137 --> 13:56.139
I need some air
outside.

13:56.183 --> 13:58.446
People are convinced
Luke's choosing Benner.

13:58.489 --> 14:00.840
- Thanks, Sara.
- Your Honor, I just have to say

14:00.883 --> 14:02.754
your mom is my "shero"!

14:02.798 --> 14:04.626
That quote was awesome.

14:04.669 --> 14:06.367
Luke is choosing who
for what?

14:07.977 --> 14:09.936
Sara?

14:09.979 --> 14:11.763
Luke's interviewing
for clerkships,

14:11.807 --> 14:13.156
including one
with Judge Benner,

14:13.200 --> 14:15.419
so I-I've got a pool going
because pools are fun

14:15.463 --> 14:17.030
and the H.O.J. can use
some fun, right?

14:17.073 --> 14:20.120
Deputy Watkins applied to be
Benner's law clerk, not mine.

14:22.949 --> 14:24.907
Ucch!

14:37.964 --> 14:39.443
Look, if this is
about another plea

14:39.487 --> 14:41.663
It's not. I wanted to

14:41.706 --> 14:44.753
I wanted to see
how you're doing.

14:44.796 --> 14:46.320
How are you doing?

14:49.453 --> 14:54.197
I want to...
share something with you.

14:54.241 --> 14:57.592
My parents left Puerto Rico
when they were newlyweds.

14:57.635 --> 15:01.030
They settled in Downey,
started a trucking company.

15:01.074 --> 15:04.033
And it was really good
for a while.

15:04.077 --> 15:07.428
But then they
they lost everything,

15:07.471 --> 15:09.952
and it got really bad.

15:09.996 --> 15:13.042
I was 16.
I was partying, and...

15:13.086 --> 15:15.740
and other stuff, stealing.

15:15.784 --> 15:18.178
II got arrested.

15:18.221 --> 15:19.657
My parents were already
struggling,

15:19.701 --> 15:21.311
and I was just
making it worse.

15:21.355 --> 15:26.795
I was on my way to juvie,
and I was just so mad

15:26.838 --> 15:28.492
at, like, everyone.

15:28.536 --> 15:30.059
It got to the point
where we

15:30.103 --> 15:31.669
we didn't speak
for, like, a year.

15:31.713 --> 15:35.325
So, Izzy, I know
what it's like

15:35.369 --> 15:36.674
Are you for real
right now?

15:36.718 --> 15:38.502
I'm just trying

15:38.546 --> 15:40.504
Trying to what?
Relate to me?

15:40.548 --> 15:43.986
Like how? A short stint
in juvie is a joke

15:44.030 --> 15:45.814
compared to four years
in maximum.

15:45.857 --> 15:47.120
And you think you know me
'cause what,

15:47.163 --> 15:49.296
we're both brown women
in the system?

15:49.339 --> 15:50.645
'Cause your parents
were pissed at you?

15:50.688 --> 15:52.429
I'm talking to you
through glass.

15:52.473 --> 15:55.911
Yeah, I'm not tryingYou don't know
the first thing about me

15:55.955 --> 15:57.521
or about life on the inside,

15:57.565 --> 15:59.436
so stick
to what you do know

15:59.480 --> 16:00.960
defending criminals
like me.

16:05.051 --> 16:07.314
Go back to my cell,
please.

16:14.843 --> 16:16.105
Thank you for the opportunity,
Judge Benner.

16:16.149 --> 16:18.107
You'll be hearing
from my J.A. soon.

16:20.588 --> 16:22.503
Sherri, I didn't hear you.

16:22.546 --> 16:24.809
I have
an astoundingly light tread.

16:24.853 --> 16:26.376
Judge Carmichael
would like a word

16:26.420 --> 16:27.812
after court adjourns
today.

16:27.856 --> 16:29.162
Thank you.

16:33.122 --> 16:34.602
I trusted you,

16:34.645 --> 16:36.386
and you let them humiliate me
in that courtroom.

16:36.430 --> 16:38.954
After what happened
in that courtr

16:38.998 --> 16:41.043
After what happened
in that courtroom,

16:41.087 --> 16:42.784
the defense lawyer offered

16:42.827 --> 16:44.046
to plea out your case
to a misdemeanor.

16:44.090 --> 16:45.613
If I agreed, Joe Collins

16:45.656 --> 16:47.180
would have gotten away
scot-free.

16:47.223 --> 16:48.529
I didn't because I believed
your story the first time,

16:48.572 --> 16:50.357
and I still do.

16:50.400 --> 16:51.619
And I'm trying to get back
your watch.

16:51.662 --> 16:53.969
Mark!You want in

16:54.013 --> 16:57.059
on the "Where will Luke clerk
in the courthouse" pool?

16:57.103 --> 16:58.713
Oh, my God. What happened?

16:58.756 --> 17:00.062
Chatty Cathy, can't you see

17:00.106 --> 17:04.066
we're having
a damn Hallmark moment here?

17:04.109 --> 17:06.286
- That wasn't nice, Bernie.
- Yeah, well, it's in the past.

17:06.329 --> 17:07.852
It literally just happened.

17:07.896 --> 17:09.637
I'm trying to tell you
something.

17:09.680 --> 17:13.858
That watch was
World War II-era Elgin

17:13.902 --> 17:15.817
that he got
from a pawn shop.

17:15.859 --> 17:18.906
The band was worn.
The case was scratched.

17:18.950 --> 17:22.040
The crown was stuck.

17:22.084 --> 17:25.740
But you see,
I love history.

17:25.782 --> 17:28.612
So Manny bought me
historical gifts.

17:28.656 --> 17:30.484
What year
was Elgin founded?

17:30.527 --> 17:33.269
1864.
Changed its name in 1874.

17:33.313 --> 17:36.664
Manuel set the watch
to Eastern time,

17:36.707 --> 17:40.320
promising that we'd be
in Niagara Falls for our 60th.

17:40.363 --> 17:43.714
We'd always wanted to go.

17:43.758 --> 17:50.460
But he died, and...
time ultimately won.

17:50.504 --> 17:55.770
Bernie, I need to re-establish
your competence on that stand.

17:55.813 --> 17:58.077
I have an idea
how I'm gonna do that.

18:00.166 --> 18:02.559
- What kind of watch was it?
- Objection. Relevance.

18:02.603 --> 18:03.821
If we travel down
this distorted memory lane,

18:03.865 --> 18:04.779
we'll be here all night.

18:04.822 --> 18:06.911
Overruled.
Witness may respond.

18:06.955 --> 18:11.177
It was an Elgin,
32-millimeter metal case.

18:11.220 --> 18:14.658
Stainless steel case back.
Rusted white dial.

18:14.702 --> 18:16.443
NATO strap was swapped out
for leather.

18:16.486 --> 18:18.053
What is Elgin?

18:18.097 --> 18:20.969
Oh, it was an Illinois-based
watch company founded in 1864.

18:21.012 --> 18:23.319
Before Elgin, all watches
were handmade.

18:23.363 --> 18:25.713
They changed the industry

18:25.756 --> 18:28.672
by mass producing watches
with machine-made parts.

18:28.716 --> 18:30.935
Men branded them
the working man's watch,

18:30.979 --> 18:34.504
as if women didn't work.
Sexist bastards.

18:34.548 --> 18:36.158
- Mrs. Morris.
- Oh, sorry, Judge.

18:36.202 --> 18:38.726
What was the watch company's
logo, Mrs. Morris?

18:38.769 --> 18:41.468
It was the Greek god Chronos
with a scythe in one hand

18:41.511 --> 18:42.860
and a pocket watch
in the other.

18:42.904 --> 18:44.993
You know, that watch isn't
worth a wooden nickel,

18:45.036 --> 18:48.649
and, like all of the other
presents Manuel gave me,

18:48.692 --> 18:51.173
I...disregarded it.

18:51.217 --> 18:53.958
But if he were here now,
I would tell him...

18:55.743 --> 18:58.441
that watch
means the world to me.

18:59.921 --> 19:02.141
Your Honor,
Mrs. Morris may be confused

19:02.184 --> 19:03.925
about recent
short-term events,

19:03.968 --> 19:06.580
but her long-term memory
is steel-trap.

19:06.623 --> 19:09.322
The defendant robbed her of one
of those priceless memories

19:09.365 --> 19:11.193
one year ago,
which any reasonable person

19:11.237 --> 19:13.413
would qualify as long term,
Given the foregoing,

19:13.456 --> 19:17.330
the People respectfully urge
the court to allow Mrs. Morris

19:17.373 --> 19:22.987
to tell her story at trial
in her own words.

19:23.031 --> 19:25.076
Nothing further. Thank you.

19:28.079 --> 19:30.821
I'll render my decision soon.

19:34.477 --> 19:36.436
Lee Ann, are you an inmate

19:36.479 --> 19:38.351
at the Central California
Women's Facility?

19:38.394 --> 19:39.526
Yeah, I am.

19:39.569 --> 19:40.744
Did you know the victim
Vera Calderon?

19:40.788 --> 19:42.093
We're...

19:42.137 --> 19:44.835
We werecellmates
for two years.

19:44.879 --> 19:46.359
And what was
your relationship like?

19:46.402 --> 19:48.143
Close. Best friends.

19:48.187 --> 19:50.276
Can you tell us what you saw
on the night in question?

19:52.321 --> 19:54.018
Vera didn't show up
at the mess hall for dinner,

19:54.062 --> 19:55.672
and we never miss a meal
together,

19:55.716 --> 19:58.849
so I looked for her,
and that's when I found her

19:58.893 --> 20:00.155
in the prison laundry room.

20:00.199 --> 20:02.201
And what did you find?

20:02.244 --> 20:04.768
Izzy was standing over
Vera's body.

20:04.812 --> 20:08.337
She saw me. She ran off.
I went to see if Vera's okay,

20:08.381 --> 20:12.428
but she wasn't breathing.

20:12.472 --> 20:14.169
You killed her.

20:14.213 --> 20:15.736
- Objection.
- Ms. Moss.

20:15.779 --> 20:16.954
You killed Vera!
You killed her!Calm down. Relax.

20:16.998 --> 20:18.956
- Hey, sit down.
- Order!

20:19.000 --> 20:20.915
Calm down. Sit down.

20:20.958 --> 20:22.090
Sit down.

20:25.528 --> 20:27.487
I think that's enough
for today.

20:27.530 --> 20:30.359
Jurors and all parties
are ordered to return tomorrow

20:30.403 --> 20:32.970
at 10:30 a.m.
Court is adjourned.

20:33.014 --> 20:35.451
I thought you said
you were gon' be cool.

20:35.495 --> 20:36.974
Step out of the box.
Hands behind your back.

20:38.324 --> 20:39.368
Okay.

20:40.630 --> 20:42.066
I got it.

20:52.468 --> 20:55.776
Izzy, tell me about
that shank again.

20:55.819 --> 20:57.299
Okay, the shank
that you described

20:57.343 --> 21:00.346
When you look at me, do you
do you see a murderer?

21:04.088 --> 21:06.787
What you said before,
me not liking you, it's not

21:06.830 --> 21:08.005
Doesn't matter.
You don't need

21:08.049 --> 21:09.529
Let me finish. Okay?

21:11.618 --> 21:13.620
At the pre-trial hearing,

21:13.663 --> 21:15.317
I noticed that you didn't
have any family

21:15.361 --> 21:16.840
sitting in the gallery,

21:16.884 --> 21:18.364
and same with this trial.

21:18.407 --> 21:21.149
What I was trying to say
before...

21:23.151 --> 21:26.720
I remember being a kid
in custody,

21:26.763 --> 21:30.767
sitting in the courtroom,
feeling really alone.

21:30.811 --> 21:33.683
And when I saw you,
I think I'm reminded

21:33.727 --> 21:37.339
of the loneliness
and the shame that...

21:37.383 --> 21:39.123
that I felt when I was 16.

21:39.167 --> 21:41.430
And now?

21:41.474 --> 21:43.476
What do you see?

21:43.519 --> 21:46.479
I see a young woman
who deserves a second chance.

21:51.527 --> 21:55.139
Okay. So...tell me
about this shank.

21:55.183 --> 21:57.838
Um...

21:57.881 --> 22:00.580
Mr. Watkins, you have been
on the front line of 802.

22:00.623 --> 22:01.972
And the experience
has been

22:02.016 --> 22:03.931
You have seen every move
I've made on the bench

22:03.974 --> 22:05.498
since I first
put on the robe.

22:05.541 --> 22:07.108
We've established a rapport,
right?

22:07.151 --> 22:08.588
Yes, Your Honor.

22:08.631 --> 22:09.980
Then why not apply
to be my clerk?

22:10.024 --> 22:11.765
I promise you
It's not personal.

22:11.808 --> 22:12.853
If one more person
says that today,

22:12.896 --> 22:14.507
it ispersonal.

22:14.550 --> 22:15.812
If you think my decision
has anything to do

22:15.856 --> 22:17.423
with that article,
I promise you,

22:17.466 --> 22:19.250
it absolutely does not.

22:23.211 --> 22:24.299
Mom.

22:24.343 --> 22:26.562
Lo. Let's talk.

22:36.006 --> 22:37.704
Mm.

22:37.747 --> 22:39.140
Hey, Dorothy Hamill.

22:39.183 --> 22:41.534
The Attorney General
folded.

22:41.577 --> 22:43.318
They're dropping
the charges against Vic.

22:43.362 --> 22:45.146
What?

22:45.189 --> 22:48.976
Your dad's gonna be released,
Mark. It's over.

22:49.019 --> 22:52.196
You okay?
You want to sit down?

22:52.240 --> 22:56.636
No. No. I...

22:56.679 --> 22:58.942
Thank you.

22:58.986 --> 23:00.814
Going to Twin Towers later
to give Vic the news,

23:00.857 --> 23:02.816
make sure the paperwork
is straight.

23:02.859 --> 23:05.253
Come with me.
I need to...

23:05.296 --> 23:07.342
I need to find
Bernie's watch.

23:07.386 --> 23:09.649
I'll meet you there.

23:12.478 --> 23:14.871
Calm down, daughter.

23:14.915 --> 23:17.091
The reporter sought meout.

23:17.134 --> 23:19.441
It wasn't
the other way around.

23:19.485 --> 23:22.836
Don't deflect, Mom. You know
this is about whatyou said.

23:22.879 --> 23:25.229
"Lola Carmichael
is a Band-Aid

23:25.273 --> 23:27.754
on Lady Justice's
gushing jugular."

23:27.797 --> 23:31.279
If growing up in a household
with me taught you anything,

23:31.322 --> 23:33.324
it's to stand firm
in what you believe.

23:33.368 --> 23:36.240
I stand by what I said.

23:36.284 --> 23:37.416
Even at the cost
of hurting your own child.

23:37.459 --> 23:40.288
You know that that was
not my intention.

23:40.331 --> 23:43.422
I believe you. I do.
But you were reckless.

23:43.465 --> 23:45.511
The reporter asked
for a statement about me.

23:45.554 --> 23:46.860
You turned this
into an indictment

23:46.903 --> 23:48.427
of the L.A. judicial system.

23:48.470 --> 23:51.734
Exactly. A system
that continues to recycle

23:51.778 --> 23:54.171
the same people of color

23:54.215 --> 23:56.522
people like you and me.

23:56.565 --> 23:59.133
Mom! I am talking
about optics,

23:59.176 --> 24:02.005
and you of all people
know about optics.

24:02.049 --> 24:05.444
And you knew better than to make
a public statement like that.

24:05.487 --> 24:08.882
Why would I not say it
in public

24:08.925 --> 24:11.493
if that is what I believe?

24:11.537 --> 24:14.975
The public has always been
my domain!

24:15.018 --> 24:16.803
And very clearly,

24:16.846 --> 24:18.935
this institution
has become yours.

24:18.979 --> 24:21.111
Yes, it has!

24:21.155 --> 24:23.940
But not in the way
that you think, Mom.

24:23.984 --> 24:26.813
With that robe,
I have the power

24:26.856 --> 24:29.859
to protect the people who are
being abused by the law

24:29.903 --> 24:32.209
and from the law
from being abused.

24:32.253 --> 24:33.602
Why can't you see that?

24:33.646 --> 24:38.085
The last time I came here,
you reminded me

24:38.128 --> 24:42.089
that my little girl
became a judge.

24:42.132 --> 24:45.832
I know who I raised then,
and I know who you are now.

24:45.875 --> 24:47.007
But you can't reconcile
the two.

24:47.050 --> 24:49.183
I didn't say that.

24:49.226 --> 24:52.708
Mom, you made me
that fire, that passion

24:52.752 --> 24:54.710
to change the world
one person at a time

24:54.754 --> 24:56.320
you gave me that.

24:56.364 --> 24:59.585
We are not in opposition.

24:59.628 --> 25:02.326
We are on the same side.

25:02.370 --> 25:04.503
You just have to accept
the fact

25:04.546 --> 25:06.548
that my tactics
are different than yours.

25:06.592 --> 25:07.984
Maybe they shouldn't be.

25:08.028 --> 25:09.856
Maybe you should be
out there with the people

25:09.899 --> 25:13.076
instead of looking down
at them.

25:19.605 --> 25:22.172
Wow.

25:23.783 --> 25:26.655
You just went there.

25:26.699 --> 25:29.528
- Lo.
- Mama, I got work to do.

25:57.773 --> 25:59.383
- Ohh!
- Bernie, it's me.

25:59.427 --> 26:02.430
Oh. What the hell's
the matter with you,

26:02.473 --> 26:05.041
sneaking up on an 80-year-old
victim of robbery?

26:05.085 --> 26:06.695
I'm sorry. I came to tell you

26:06.739 --> 26:09.350
the judge is gonna let you
testify at trial.

26:09.393 --> 26:12.745
You did good, Bernie.
Your husband would be proud.

26:12.788 --> 26:14.094
Want a beer?

26:14.137 --> 26:16.531
Ah, I'm good, but thanks.

26:16.575 --> 26:18.228
Take my word for it.
You need a drink.

26:22.145 --> 26:24.278
Manny loved fishing.

26:24.321 --> 26:26.585
Never had the skill
or the luck for it,

26:26.628 --> 26:28.021
but he would sit there
for hours.

26:28.064 --> 26:30.110
Me, I'm too impatient.

26:30.153 --> 26:32.025
So if you think
I'm gonna...

26:32.068 --> 26:33.766
fish for what's wrong
with you...

26:36.899 --> 26:41.121
My dad and I,
wewe don't, um...

26:41.164 --> 26:43.602
Anyway, he got himself
into some trouble,

26:43.645 --> 26:47.780
and I helped him get out
of it because, well...

26:47.823 --> 26:52.132
right now we're right back
to where we started,

26:52.175 --> 26:56.440
I guess I just thought
it would be different.

26:56.484 --> 27:01.054
It's strange.
It's the most time

27:01.097 --> 27:02.795
we've spent together
in years.

27:02.838 --> 27:05.493
That's not strange.
It's life.

27:07.843 --> 27:09.366
I mean, losing time
is the worst thing

